item.title: CVE-2023-2026|2024-08-02T06:12:19.742Z -- unknown -- image%20protector
item.description: The Image Protector WordPress plugin through 1.1 does not properly sanitize some of its settings, which could allow high-privilege users to perform Stored Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attacks even when the unfiltered_html capability is disallowed (for example in multisite setup).
